==English==
===Etymology===
*[[Diminutive]] of [[smile]].

===Pronunciation===
*SAMPA: /<tt>"smaIli</tt>/

===Noun===
'''smiley''' (''plural'' '''smileys''')
{{wikipedia}}
#A simplified representation of a smiling face, usually as two dots for the eyes and an arc for the mouth.
#(''Internet'') A combination of keyboard characters used to gives a graphical representation of a person's mood or emotion, not necessarily a smile.
#(slang) Having one's throat slit from side to side. 

====Synonyms====
*(1): [[smiley face]]
*(2): [[emoticon]]

